post_cb({"10509685": {"CommentCount": "2", "ViewCount": "1736", "PostTypeId": "1", "ClosedDate": "2012-05-29T04:35:45.970", "LastEditorUserId": "-1", "CreationDate": "2012-05-09T04:07:46.620", "LastActivityDate": "2012-05-09T08:34:18.943", "Title": "sizeof(bool) g++ vs vc++", "AcceptedAnswerId": "10512325", "LastEditDate": "2017-05-23T11:43:57.187", "Id": "10509685", "Score": "-4", "Body": "<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_10509685_10509685_0\"><strong>Possible Duplicate:</strong><br>\n<a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/4897844/is-sizeofbool-implementation-defined-in-c\">Is sizeof(bool) implementation defined in C++?</a> </br></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Im writing code that is compiled in vc++ with a g++ lib (libpng) and need to know if bool is the same size and bits in g++ and vc++. All I know is false is all 0's and that sizeof(bool) is 1 in vc++</p>\n", "Tags": "<visual-c++><g++><boolean><sizeof><bits>", "OwnerUserId": "1350209", "AnswerCount": "2"}, "10511913": {"ParentId": "10509685", "PostTypeId": "2", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>As you can read in <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/5067492/why-the-sizeofbool-is-not-defined-to-be-one-by-the-standard-itself\">another question</a> C++03 Standard $5.3.3/1 says,</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_10509685_10511913_0\">sizeof(char), sizeof(signed char) and sizeof(unsigned char) are 1; the result of sizeof applied to any other fundamental type (3.9.1) is implementation-defined. [Note: in particular,sizeof(bool) and sizeof(wchar_t) are implementation-defined.69)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>so the result of <code>sizeof(bool)</code> is implementation defined.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "1365671", "LastEditorUserId": "-1", "LastEditDate": "2017-05-23T12:22:22.627", "Id": "10511913", "Score": "2", "CreationDate": "2012-05-09T07:48:56.610", "LastActivityDate": "2012-05-09T07:48:56.610"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_10509685_10511913_0": {"section_id": 6076, "quality": 0.7058823529411765, "length": 12}}, "n3337": {"so_10509685_10511913_0": {"section_id": 5844, "quality": 0.7058823529411765, "length": 12}}, "n4659": {"so_10509685_10511913_0": {"section_id": 7572, "quality": 0.7058823529411765, "length": 12}}}, "10512325": {"ParentId": "10509685", "PostTypeId": "2", "CommentCount": "11", "Body": "<p>There are versions of <code>g++</code> (and versions of Visual C++ as well for that matter) for which on some platforms <code>sizeof(bool)</code> is not equal to 1. So no, you can't assume that it will be the same on g++ and Visual C++. You can't even assume that it's the same on different versions of the same compiler or the same version on different platforms.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "149392", "LastEditorUserId": "149392", "LastEditDate": "2012-05-09T08:34:18.943", "Id": "10512325", "Score": "3", "CreationDate": "2012-05-09T08:18:56.080", "LastActivityDate": "2012-05-09T08:34:18.943"}});